g.title: EleanorRank3Convo1 begins.
g.text: EleanorRank3Convo1 begins.

g.title: j1352040185
g.text: Hey, Eleanor, is it okay to ask you about the telepathy thing?

g.title: j449956871
g.text: So, what's it like being able to peek into everybody's heads?

g.title: j3997711563
g.text: It’s always okay to ask, so long as you ask politely.

g.title: j2929484050
g.text: Excuse me?

g.title: j1676763719
g.text: Some people find that very difficult.

g.title: j270108603
g.text: Is that what you imagine I do? Casually violate other people's privacy?

g.title: j2233772352
g.text: Do you hear people’s thoughts without trying? Or do you always have to make an effort to get inside their head?

g.title: j3266173003
g.text: Is it like a light switch? Or is it always "stuck on?"

g.title: j346282164
g.text: If that's what you think of me, then I doubt we have much to talk about.

g.title: j1724950120
g.text: Yes to both. If I just sit and ‘listen’, I can pick up on internal monologues and strong feelings.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j3504897963
g.text: The hardest part is filtering out the LOUD stuff I don’t want to know about.

g.title: j782057195
g.text: I don’t always get to experience feelings as if they were someone else’s. The more pre-verbal it is, the harder it is to discern between ‘them’ and ‘me’.

g.title: j2501553523
g.text: Permission to delve into the realms of ‘too much information’?

g.title: j900991913
g.text: Well I'm too curious to say no, now...

g.title: j1750910352
g.text: Permission granted.

g.title: j2043439775
g.text: Eh... another time, maybe. [End.]

g.title: j1516279387
g.text: I salute your bravery.

g.title: j3856473036
g.text: Read further at your own risk.

g.title: j3791049990
g.text: Not long after we all got the Entrati shots, I thought I had some kind of secondary bladder infection. Mate. I was up and down off that couch like a yo-yo. I even had Lettie hunting me down cranberry juice and mineral water.

g.title: j3219934500
g.text: Turns out I was just feeling six people’s natural biological urges. My nervous system naturally assumed they were mine.

g.title: j4077135833
g.text: Which was worse? Learning you weren't catastrophically sick or...

g.title: j3076592125
g.text: Must have been a relief to find out the truth.

g.title: j1387067423
g.text: Well, I AM catastrophically sick. Let's not mince words. But I'd rather be saddled with telepathy than never-ending cystitis.

g.title: j471057206
g.text: I learned to build walls around my mind after that incident. Lettie sometimes finds meds that can shut the whole telepathic side of me down, just for a few hours. I have a stash of them, but I don’t take them unless I really, really need to sleep.

g.title: j1245760813
g.text: It’s such a useful talent to have, that’s the problem. Arthur insists on seeing it as a strategic asset.

g.title: j1678243829
g.text: What about people’s privacy? Isn’t it bad for morale?

g.title: j1689018792
g.text: But what if somebody *doesn't* want their head invaded?

g.title: j1610443516
g.text: It’s bloody awful for morale.

g.title: j2357463734
g.text: Even if I insist that I can control it, do you think they would believe me?

g.title: j2328955282
g.text: None of us is soft. We’re used to roughing it. This place is a five star hotel compared to a regular Britannic army barracks.

g.title: j2543259300
g.text: You shower together, you eat together, et cetera. You get used to one another. You have to.

g.title: j2470134812
g.text: But as Arthur would say, there’s a sodding limit.

g.title: j2399074832
g.text: So how do you deal with it?

g.title: j1838829532
g.text: I just don’t let them know how much of their inner lives I hear, see and feel. I don’t go probing uninvited, whatever Lettie might think.

g.title: j3231332801
g.text: Sometimes one of them will have a thought, and immediately think ‘did she hear me thinking that?' It's kinder to let them wonder. What they don’t know can’t hurt them.

g.title: j991542868
g.text: Have you overheard any of MY thoughts?

g.title: j4070318203
g.text: So... what've you picked up in my head?

g.title: j1018533342
g.text: Like I said, I’m not about to confirm or deny anything.

g.title: j1925647639
g.text: I should say, right about now, that there’s another important reason why I keep this shit to myself.

g.title: j4183271119
g.text: Go on…

g.title: j1538361658
g.text: So. Arthur and me. We’re on the streets, raiding a Scaldra cache, and he’s seriously off his game. He’s not shooting straight, he’s driving like a drunk duck at the dodgems, he can’t even do the sword thing.

g.title: j3363202762
g.text: Naturally, I tell him to get his act together. Immediately he starts blaming ME. He tells me I’m always acting so superior, don’t I understand the pressure of command, if I had the first idea what he has to deal with on a DAILY basis I’d buckle, all this self-pitying bollocks.

g.title: j1446753449
g.text: Check boolean EleanorHeroVirus

g.title: j1525073739
g.text: Remember the Hero Virus I told you about?

g.title: j1446753449->j1525073739
g.text: true

g.title: j1117155717
g.text: I have this theory I call the Hero Virus.

g.title: j1446753449->j1117155717
g.text: false

g.title: j4030251901
g.text: Terminal case.

g.title: j2500125924
g.text: Little boys get it into their heads that the stories they've been fed are how the world really works. They think they are the hero and everything revolves around them.

g.title: j2502292150
g.text: Everything was about Arthur.

g.title: j3317640572
g.text: Arthur has one of the worst cases of Hero Virus I've ever seen.

g.title: j3366861135
g.text: So I fire back at him ‘you know I can tell when you’re thinking about Aoi, right?’

g.title: j2182426742
g.text: Boolean EleanorHeroVirus is now true.

g.title: j905596592
g.text: Ouch.

g.title: j2607016816
g.text: Yeah.

g.title: j356850723
g.text: Not my proudest moment.

g.title: j1267351221
g.text: Even if he hadn’t been my brother, that was a shitty thing to do. I’ll never do it again.

g.title: j3405043863
g.text: How did he react?

g.title: j1105640712
g.text: … I don’t like that you want to know.

g.title: j2118298541
g.text: Now I’m wondering whether you’re enjoying the idea of Arthur being humiliated.

g.title: j2836734348
g.text: Please don’t let that be it. I’m starting to like you, and this is the sort of thing I wouldn’t be able to look past.

g.title: j3754948893
g.text: I’m asking because I like the guy.

g.title: j1954363620
g.text: Yikes. That wasn't my intention. I just wanted to know how someone like that reacts to being confronted.

g.title: j1300673418
g.text: I am enjoying it. Sounds like Arthur had it coming.

g.title: j4158931108
g.text: Okay. That’s understandable. I’m sorry I snapped.

g.title: j1655493795
g.text: I didn't just confront him. I HURT him.

g.title: j3441908462
g.text: Oh, I get it.

g.title: j2954870624
g.text: He crumpled. I felt horrible.

g.title: j810981587
g.text: Arthur's used to being talked back to. Just look at Quincy!

g.title: j344852774
g.text: Arthur's a pain in the arse.

g.title: j58416970
g.text: I’d broken something important between us. Hang on. I need to tell you something so you’ll understand.

g.title: j2571420740
g.text: But we all know Arthur's got walls up. He acts like he's impossible to hurt.

g.title: j3054088538
g.text: But when I'm trying to talk to you about something I feel guilty about...

g.title: j3565272654
g.text: When we were little, some older boys stole Arthur’s favourite Action Angus and threw him on the Solstice bonfire.

g.title: j2956212194
g.text: I could feel how shocked and confused he was. He'd thought he was safe around me. Not anymore.

g.title: j2354243318
g.text: Never mind.

g.title: j686919634
g.text: I can still see him bent over and the flesh coloured plastic bubbling and dripping all over his camo trousers.

g.title: j2101830647
g.text: Check boolean DrifterSiblingYes

g.title: j1049424244
g.text: I don't miss being a kid.

g.title: j241741063
g.text: Yay, childhood.

g.title: j3958087337
g.text: Я знаю, як це — скривдити брата чи сестру. У мене… колись була.

g.title: j2101830647->j3958087337
g.text: true

g.title: j4028813067
g.text: Check boolean DrifterSiblingNo

g.title: j2101830647->j4028813067
g.text: false

g.title: j2840715800
g.text: The boys laughed and said Arthur should be happy. Action Angus was going to the Hall of Heroes for the midwinter feast like warriors used to. I wanted to murder them. Little bastards.

g.title: j905462389
g.text: Boolean DrifterSiblingYes is now true.

g.title: j4028813067->j3958087337
g.text: true

g.title: j4028813067->j3958087337
g.text: false

g.title: j2004595963
g.text: Sounds like you hurt him badly.

g.title: j4028813067->j2004595963
g.text: true

g.title: j4028813067->j2004595963
g.text: false

g.title: j2865018869
g.text: Arthur didn’t want the boys to see him cry, and he didn’t want to cry in front of my dad, so the only person left was me. His shitty big sister.

g.title: j307075216
g.text: It's horrible, isn't it? You get so used to the ritual of it, putting one another down, sniping and snarking...

g.title: j12400804
g.text: Yeah, I did. I apologized, I promised I’d never do anything like that again, but I still feel like shit because of it.

g.title: j705054154
g.text: I’m telling you about that because that’s where Arthur went, in his head. He remembered feeling like it was safe to cry in front of me if he ever really NEEDED to, and now?

g.title: j4154338950
g.text: It's comforting, almost. Then one day you draw blood and you can't take it back.

g.title: j2133980303
g.text: It’s fighting dirty.

g.title: j3107746077
g.text: Now it wasn’t safe any more.

g.title: j874526371
g.text: YES.

g.title: j3691783314
g.text: You GET IT. I love that! Fighting dirty.

g.title: j561598693
g.text: You know that thing where you’re in an argument with someone and once it’s all over, you think of the exact right thing you should have said?

g.title: j1668124527
g.text: I don’t get that any more. I have a magic I Win button. All I’d have to do is look into their brain, grab whatever they’re most ashamed of and rub it in their face.

g.title: j4273687225
g.text: And I CAN’T DO IT, no matter how much I want to. Because I’m supposed to be a ‘good person’.

g.title: j1420133452
g.text: This isn’t about trying to be a saint, Eleanor. It’s not even about being a hero. It’s about refusing to be an asshole.

g.title: j2211808360
g.text: We're all trying to do the right thing here. Is it really that much harder for you?

g.title: j244925839
g.text: We all have lines we won’t cross and this is one of yours. I respect that.

g.title: j3415131053
g.text: Oh dear. That's what I get for parading my virtues, isn't it?

g.title: j324979062
g.text: Thank you.

g.title: j3721733228
g.text: Sorry. I was expecting sympathy. But I'll take the reality check.

g.title: j211091668
g.text: I’m not looking for sympathy. Truly.

g.title: j526755082
g.text: It's not like I'm the only one who has to keep her powers in check, is it? We're all time bombs waiting to go off.

g.title: j3437439291
g.text: I just wanted someone else to understand. Honestly, I’m a little taken aback by how much you DO understand.

g.title: j581575261
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j3018643092
g.text: You didn’t have to listen. But I’m glad you did.

g.title: j724650308
g.text: Appreciate the talk.

g.title: j2510420239
g.text: It’s a messed-up freakshow inside this skull of mine. I think you can appreciate why I don’t roll out the welcome mat to strangers.

g.title: j1663455968
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j2923476304
g.text: I expect people to run away screaming. You haven’t. Yet. I wonder why. Thank you. Again. For everything.
